1EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"89136BAD883F4B5FBD7D949EEE5C4BD0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2CC0C7B81E914832B8DF45EF890A49AE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Plunge freeze the neurons: <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156523,"guid":"67ECC330964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156522,"previous_guid":"61A084D0964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5C1920B29B2242AAA2A606F1E37D6357","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D24494E4F3D341C0B1B3EEA008378DD4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">First, exchange the medium to neuronal medium containing 10 % glycerol to ensure good vitrification (see also Baeuerlein et al., Cell, 2017). <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156524,"guid":"71803D50964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156523,"previous_guid":"67ECC330964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"98CFAB0108A443BF8A9F6F9FD0ACA437","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6A6CFF2A3248430586C68780D795887F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Hold the grids carefully with plunging tweezers and insert the tweezers in the holder of the Vitrobot (Thermofisher). Make sure grids are blotted from the front as well as from the back with Whatman paper. Use a humidity of 80 % and a temperature of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, a blot force of 10 and blot time of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"9019F300964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":37,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"3F99A9F0964F11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":10,"title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"A28B869E1BD34CC0BBC3035B7FECEFFD","order_id":4,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prepare the Vitrobot prior to exchanging the neuronal medium to ensure fast plunge-freezing and only short incubation of the neurons in 10 % glycerol (around 5 min).<\/span><span> For preparing the Vitrobot, turn it on, apply the settings you want to use, add liquid nitrogen (LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>) into the LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>container and liquefy the ethane \/ propane gas in the cavity that is cooled by LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>).<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":10},{"id":1156525,"guid":"B2F60D50964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156524,"previous_guid":"71803D50964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4DC808DC73FA4CA4A0FB3E60FA4E04D1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9F0C2D6B637B4E709FCA012E710631C6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>After plunging, store EM grids in appropriate EM grid boxes in LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156526,"guid":"C3256C70964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156525,"previous_guid":"B2F60D50964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0491A37BAC1941A789DD4F941C5C63F0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DF9BC826454D45E299FE6A8E9FC75733","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For cryo-fluorescence microscopy, clip EM grids in autogrid holders with cut-out to enable FIB-milling under LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>. Place clip ring on top of EM grid in the back of the autogrid frame, cells facing downwards to enable FIB-milling of the cells later on.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156527,"guid":"CDB520E0964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156526,"previous_guid":"C3256C70964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"80004B30E53D49E1BFD707ABF8C0F3F3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"087A459D81F3451BB3C3F75EC219A117","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer clipped grids into shuttles of the CorrSight (Thermofisher) microscope. Cells facing again downward.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156528,"guid":"D68BDAB0964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156527,"previous_guid":"CDB520E0964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"13558AD6963E4F51850F90D0F1127EF8","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D9BAED6F3AAC4B2EAF72252BC5B70E8D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer shuttles into CorrSight shuttle boxes and bring the grids to the microscope. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156529,"guid":"E33F8090964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156528,"previous_guid":"D68BDAB0964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EF14125F75E245978FB0179ECC8795E9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6B6E4331DD6D44E7BFBB0C766B6F24D5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Move the shuttle into the cryo-box of the cooled-down CorrSight microscope. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"47A06D77220E4328B5DAB81308140508","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For cooling down, the tank in the back of the cryo-box is filled with LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>and the slowly evaporating LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> gas is led through the box to the outside, cooling the atmosphere in the box to a temperature of -180 \u00b0C.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156530,"guid":"01A46AA0964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156529,"previous_guid":"E33F8090964D11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FFEBEC9D60F54AC98189F89926B1D9E9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4FE433343F78456A8856CB1E62C5B816","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Open the LA software and the MAPS software, create a new project in MAPS and find areas of interest in the specimen at 5 x magnification. Take overview images of the EM grids in DIC mode as well as in fluorescence mode (choose channel depending on your fluorophore).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":[{"id":9,"title":"Imaging","icon":"ImagingIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156531,"guid":"0BE62620964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156530,"previous_guid":"01A46AA0964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"044D96F142F54CDBA66025B799FE2305","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F68D677110514615ABC21145BC193A0F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Find cells that look promising (they should be close to the center of the grid and should be located in the middle of a square but not on the EM grid bar) and acquire 20 x or 40 x images, depending on the size of the feature of interest. The MAPS project will be saved automatically.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":[{"id":9,"title":"Imaging","icon":"ImagingIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156532,"guid":"141A1040964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156531,"previous_guid":"0BE62620964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EF801CBFA33348A7A28B31B3BFF01A25","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C3D810BE0C9F4CAE84912DCFEE7B389C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>After imaging of the grids, take them carefully out of the cryo-box and place them in LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156533,"guid":"1E7CE850964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156532,"previous_guid":"141A1040964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F4D96F74F3924CDEA791CF02CB5FE1CA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EBF466A904F5455BAADD6CBA23B42932","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Move the MAPS project to the computer of the FIB instrument (Scios or Quanta, Thermofisher).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156534,"guid":"226F7F40964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156533,"previous_guid":"1E7CE850964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C71355E003144C358544086A15ABFBB2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"56328419499A4C9D8FBBC9FFB571611C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Transfer the EM grids from the CorrSight shuttles into the FIB shuttle under LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>. Grids should be inserted into the shuttle with cells facing towards the experimenter and the cut-out should face upright. Transfer the EM grids subsequently under vacuum into the FIB chamber and place them onto the stage which is cooled by nitrogen gas, which is led through a liquid nitrogen container and cooled to LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>temperature.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156535,"guid":"2A097350964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156534,"previous_guid":"226F7F40964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C5FF963880364371A680891083DAFF6E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"88F94643CBDE4A6CBBCB70BC9AF4BC3E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Coat the grids with organic platinum to avoid damage of the sample by out-of-focus gallium ions. Tilt the stage to 18 \u00b0 to allow milling at a shallow angle.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156536,"guid":"30B64840964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156535,"previous_guid":"2A097350964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"44B0FDCEBEC74D26890EAC46B9EC6DFA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"76377EAC07134BCB99513E99E9CC24C1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Find the eucentric height of the stage, by correlating the SEM and FIB image and moving the stage iteratively. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156537,"guid":"34BE8A10964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156536,"previous_guid":"30B64840964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3FDB77CF81204789B8D80471719F36E2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4D6456EEC9F143F78122EBE1D09D1AF0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Open MAPS software at the FIB computer and take an overview image of the EM grid with the SEM beam. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156538,"guid":"38F44480964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156537,"previous_guid":"34BE8A10964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"69AC6AB87377442685C6B6A5494E5B94","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8B922F65DB5C480CAEA4D1CF1B97097C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Load the SEM image into the MAPS software (on some instruments where MAPS and the FIB can communicate directly, the image will be automatically uploaded into the software). Apply the three-point-method of correlation to the grid (see also Guo et al., Cell, 2018).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156539,"guid":"3E9EC4A0964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156538,"previous_guid":"38F44480964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E285A08461C3458AB387BD708AA0D7B0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"25C9579BD9654C0E8C9A7A582599BC79","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For the three-point-method click with the right mouse button onto \u2018Align\u2019. Select three alignment markers and place them on the SEM as well as on the fluorescence image on points that can be easily recognized (e.g. broken carbon or corners of grid bars). Click \u2018finish\u2019 when you are done and the two images will be overlaid.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156540,"guid":"43322F70964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156539,"previous_guid":"3E9EC4A0964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C5CBE426C46146F89FE5D36B34231557","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"21674BDDFE624AE78EE7C290EB38F99A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Then find the cells of interest and zoom in with the SEM. Take again a SEM image and correlate that with the fluorescence image (take care to be in eucentric height and now use the 20 x or 40 x image). Use again the three-point-method to make sure you find the correct cell and region of interest (Figure 1 b, Figure 2 a-c). Do that iteratively until fluorescence image and SEM image match perfectly.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db2u9nan.jpg\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db2w9nan.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"58BDAD34DB3844B19F0F1F9C206BA6D1","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db2u9nan.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"76FA1BD7BDBC48B9A243E2F1E8EEA067","order_id":3,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db2w9nan.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":[{"id":9,"title":"Imaging","icon":"ImagingIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156541,"guid":"47E29820964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156540,"previous_guid":"43322F70964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8B12CE4338434C6D92935C25D21A4277","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"437BDA43362043F8AD44C422177AF8C1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Image the cell in the FIB beam and start with the milling process (Figure 1 c). For milling start with a high current of 0.5 nA at 30 kV and go down to 50 pA for fine milling.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db2y9nan.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"940E29337A9741B7A110EAC265AEAF3B","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db2y9nan.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":[{"id":9,"title":"Imaging","icon":"ImagingIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156542,"guid":"54E03F50964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156541,"previous_guid":"47E29820964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"65CCFDF82ED748DBA5E751B1ADA72DEA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BAD0E450650240FFA4A1FD0BBB65983D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Mill as long as you get a thin transparent lamella, which is roughly 100 to 150 nm in height. Double check the thickness of the lamellas by imaging it at 3 kV in the SEM. It should be transparent at 3 kV to be sufficiently thin. Every time the stage is moved, repeat the three-point-method, to make sure you still target the correct area.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156543,"guid":"5A24F8C0964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156542,"previous_guid":"54E03F50964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"137797A22A9F4BCA95F8EB4AD8D91889","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D51A1A66920F453CAF53CD13C3DD9B54","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After the milling, transfer the grids out of the FIB under vacuum and store the grids in suitable EM grid boxes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1156544,"guid":"5E0CBA40964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","previous_id":1156543,"previous_guid":"5A24F8C0964E11EBBDF479DF06FED79F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B620F32464B14A09A58AC0F407A79963","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Correlative Light-Electron Microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein Aggregates in Primary Neurons"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7A408BE33F2F4BFFA3DBA1ACB7F35F85","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">During your next TEM session: Transfer the grids from the boxes into the TEM and acquire tomograms at areas of interest (Figure 1 e and f).<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db229nan.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"241800C10E6D45C293FEEBBD7A07A36E","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/db229nan.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":40,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol details methods for correlative light-electron microscopy of \u03b1-synuclein aggregates in primary neurons.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1617836311}